12 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 3 and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 3. 5 MRSA §2041, sub-§10, as repealed and replaced by PL 2021, c. 293, Pt.
14 A, §5, is amended to read:
15 10. Advisory council. A 12-member 13-member advisory council is established to
16 advise the board on establishing annual spending targets pursuant to section 2042,
17 subsection 1 and determining methods for meeting those spending targets pursuant to
18 section 2042, subsection 3. The advisory council consists of:
19 A. The Governor or the governor's designee;
20 B. The Commissioner of Administrative and Financial Services or the commissioner's
21 designee;
22 C. The Commissioner of Corrections or the commissioner's designee;
23 D. The Commissioner of Health and Human Services or the commissioner's designee;
24 E. The Attorney General or the Attorney General's designee;
25 F. The Executive Director of Employee Health and Benefits, within the Department
26 of Administrative and Financial Services, Bureau of Human Resources, or the
27 executive director's designee;
28 G. A representative from the Maine State Service Employees Association, appointed
29 by the Governor, based on a nomination by the association;
30 H. A representative from the Maine Education Association, appointed by the
31 Governor, based on a nomination by the association;
32 I. A representative from the Maine Municipal Association, appointed by the Governor,
33 based on a nomination by the association;
