35 SUMMARY
3366 This amendment is the majority report of the committee. The amendment makes the
3377 following changes to the bill related to the provisions governing the Maine Prescription
3388 Drug Affordability Board.
39 1. It adds a member representing health insurance carriers to the advisory council to
40 the Maine Prescription Drug Affordability Board.
Page 3 - 132LR0293(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 314, L.D. 697
1 2. It amends the provision in the bill relating to the consideration by the board of
2 prescription drug spending data to clarify that the board must use prescription drug
3 spending data from the Maine Health Data Organization and publicly available data
4 available for purchase or for free and, if there is additional prescription drug spending data
5 required by the board and its staff, the amendment authorizes the board to recommend that
6 the Maine Health Data Organization may collect this data by rule.
7 The amendment also makes a related change to the provisions governing the Maine
8 Health Data Organization to clarify that the Maine Health Data Organization may share
9 data with board staff.
